        <question>
            <text>Area of region {(x, y) : x^2 + y^2 &lt;= 2ax, y^2 &gt;= ax, x, y &gt;= 0}:</text>
            <option id="A">a^2(pi/4 - 2/3)</option><option id="B">None</option><option id="C">C</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Semicircle and parabola intersection.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>The area of the curve y = |x-1| and line y=3 is:</text>
            <option id="A">9</option><option id="B">4.5</option><option id="C">3</option><option id="D">None</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Triangle with base 6 and height 3. Area = 1/2 * 6 * 3 = 9.</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Area of the loop of y^2 = x^2(2-x):</text>
