        <question>
            <text>Area bounded by y = e^x, y = e^{-x} and line x = 1:</text>
            <option id="A">e + 1/e - 2</option><option id="B">e - 1/e</option><option id="C">None</option><option id="D">D</option>
            <answer>A</answer><explanation>Integral 0 to 1 (e^x - e^{-x}) dx = [e^x + e^{-x}] = (e + 1/e) - (1 + 1).</explanation></question>
        <question>
            <text>Area of region bounded by y = x, y = 2x and x = 3:</text>
